OL,3,CCouncil calls on Government to provide
OL,4,Caid to victims of New Years flooding
OL,6,F"Secondly, in the absence of this
OL,7,Ffunding, will you provide urgently
OL,8,Fneeded resources to help those
OL,9,Fresidents and businesses who are in
OL,10,Fdire need of central Government
OL,11,Ffinancial support?"
OL,13,FAs a result of the flooding, residents
OL,14,Fwere left without electricity,
OL,15,Fheating, and water, with emergency
OL,16,Fservices rescuing a number of tenants
OL,17,Ftrapped inside the building.
OL,19,FOnce out of the mill, residents were
OL,20,Fleft with no option other than staying
OL,21,Fwith friends or family members.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
